Description: CVE-2026-12064 - curl tool: honor --proto-default for SSH verification
 When invoked with a schemeless URL together with --proto-default sftp
 (or scp), the tool layer misidentified the scheme and skipped setting
 CURLOPT_SSH_HOST_PUBLIC_KEY_SHA256 and CURLOPT_SSH_KNOWNHOSTS. libcurl
 honored CURLOPT_DEFAULT_PROTOCOL and proceeded, so curl connected to an
 unverified SSH remote. Backport of upstream commit ab3bb8cd
 (config2setopts.c) to 7.74.0's tool_operate.c.
 .
 Notes on this backport:
  * The upstream fix lives in src/config2setopts.c which does not exist
    in 7.74.0; the equivalent logic is in src/tool_operate.c. In 7.74.0
    the SSH options (CURLOPT_SSH_KNOWNHOSTS et al.) are gated on the
    global `built_in_protos` capability bitmask rather than on a
    per-URL parsed scheme, so the class of bug reported against later
    curl releases (per-URL scheme guessed as HTTP when --proto-default
    sftp is set) does not manifest identically in 7.74.0. However, in
    the defensive spirit of the upstream fix we also require the
    SSH_KNOWNHOSTS block to be entered whenever `--proto-default` names
    scp/sftp, so that a future refactor which narrows the gate to a
    per-URL scheme in this file cannot silently regress the fix.
  * CURLOPT_SSH_HOST_PUBLIC_KEY_SHA256 does not exist in libcurl 7.74.0
    (added in 7.80.0) - the sha256-hostkey setopt from the upstream
    diff is intentionally omitted; hostpubmd5 handling is unchanged.
  * The CURLU_NO_GUESS_SCHEME flag used by the upstream fix does not
    exist in 7.74.0's URL API - it is not needed for this backport
    because 7.74.0's tool_operate.c does not parse the URL scheme via
    curl_url_get() at the point of SSH-option-setting.
  * Regression test tests/data/test1725 (SCP with --proto-default SCP
    that fails on a bad host key) is included, adapted to 7.74.0's
    test harness (%SSH_PWD substitution, curl_client_key in the
    working directory).
  * tests/data/test1724 is NOT included: it exercises the IPFS gateway
    codepath which does not exist in 7.74.0 (no --ipfs-gateway).
  * tests/data/test2036 is NOT overwritten: 7.74.0's test2036 is an
    unrelated HTTP -O regression test; replacing it would drop existing
    coverage.
  * docs/cmdline-opts/proto-default.md is NOT ported: 7.74.0 uses the
    older .d docs format and the change is cosmetic (a note about the
    argument shape and IPFS exclusion), not security-relevant.
  * The tests/data/Makefile.inc hunk uses tight context (test1660 /
    blank / test1700 line / blank / test1800) to remain fuzz-0 after
    earlier CVE patches (notably CVE-2024-7264-1) add test1656 to a
    nearby line.
