Description: CVE-2026-6429 - Fix netrc credential leak on redirect via proxy
 When libcurl is configured to use a .netrc file for credentials and follow
 HTTP redirects through a proxy, credentials for the first host could be
 leaked to the redirected-to host. This happened because conn->bits.netrc
 bypassed the same-host auth check entirely, causing Authorization headers
 to be sent unconditionally on redirects when credentials came from netrc.
 .
 Debian bullseye curl 7.74.0 already routes redirect auth decisions through
 Curl_allow_auth_to_host(), which compares hostname, port, and protocol.
 This backport removes the remaining netrc bypass so netrc credentials are
 subject to the same checks as other auth sources.
