+# Why You Cannot Fix `curl` CVE-2023-23914 via Code Patching in Containers
+
+## Overview: What Is CVE-2023-23914?
+
+CVE-2023-23914 is a vulnerability in curl versions prior to 7.88.0 related to HSTS (HTTP Strict Transport Security) functionality. The issue causes HSTS mechanisms to fail when multiple URLs are requested serially, potentially allowing cleartext transmission of sensitive information.
+
+**Technical Details:**
+- **Component:** HSTS functionality in libcurl
+- **Issue:** HSTS state not properly carried between subsequent transfers on the same command line
+- **Impact:** HTTPS enforcement may be bypassed, leading to potential cleartext transmission
+- **Affected Versions:** curl < 7.88.0 with HSTS support enabled
+
+---
+
+## Why CVE-2023-23914 Is a **FALSE POSITIVE** for Debian Bullseye
+
+### 🔹 1. HSTS Support Not Compiled in Debian Bullseye
+
+According to the [Debian Security Tracker](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2023-23914):
+
+- **Debian bullseye**: curl 7.74.0-1.3+deb11u13 - **`<ignored>` (curl is not built with HSTS support)**
+- **Status**: The vulnerable HSTS functionality is **not included** in the Debian bullseye curl build
+- **Conclusion**: ✅ **Cannot be exploited** - the vulnerable code path does not exist
+
+### 🔹 2. Build Configuration Excludes Vulnerable Feature
+
+- Debian bullseye's curl package was compiled **without HSTS support**
+- The vulnerable HSTS state management code is not present in the binary
+- This is a deliberate build-time decision by Debian package maintainers
+- Scanners cannot detect build-time feature exclusions, only version numbers
+
+### 🔹 3. Version vs. Feature Mismatch
+
+- **Package Version**: 7.74.0-1.3+deb11u13 (appears vulnerable by version)
+- **Build Reality**: No HSTS support = no vulnerability exposure
+- **Scanner Limitation**: Tools flag based on version ranges, not compiled features
+- **Result**: False positive due to feature absence
+
+---
+
+## **Recommended Action: Mark as False Positive**
+
+This CVE should be marked as a **False Positive** because:
+
+1. **Feature Not Built**: The HSTS functionality containing the vulnerability is not compiled into Debian bullseye curl
+2. **Code Path Unreachable**: The vulnerable HSTS state management code cannot be executed
+3. **Scanner Limitation**: SCA tools cannot detect build-time feature exclusions
+4. **No Action Required**: The vulnerability cannot be exploited as the functionality is absent
+
+## **Specific CVE Details: CVE-2023-23914**
+
+**CVE ID**: CVE-2023-23914  
+**Package**: curl  
+**Debian bullseye Version**: 7.74.0-1.3+deb11u13  
+**Status**: **FALSE POSITIVE** - HSTS functionality not built in distribution
+
+### **Description**
+**HSTS functionality fail when multiple URLs are requested serially**
+
+A cleartext transmission of sensitive information vulnerability exists in curl <v7.88.0 that could cause HSTS functionality to fail when multiple URLs are requested serially. Using its HSTS support, curl can be instructed to use HTTPS instead of using an insecure clear-text HTTP step even when HTTP is provided in the URL. This HSTS mechanism would however surprisingly be ignored by subsequent transfers when done on the same command line because the state would not be properly carried on.
+
+**Technical Details:**
+- **Introduced by**: [commit 7385610](https://github.com/curl/curl/commit/7385610d0c74c6a254fea5e4cd6e1d559d848c8c) (curl-7_74_0)
+- **Fixed by**: curl 7.88.0+ via [PR #10138](https://github.com/curl/curl/pull/10138)
+- **Root Cause**: HSTS state not properly maintained between sequential transfers
+
+### **Why This Is a False Positive for Debian Bullseye**
+1. **HSTS Not Compiled**: The curl package in Debian bullseye lacks HSTS support entirely
+2. **Feature Absence**: The vulnerable functionality simply does not exist in the binary
+3. **Build Decision**: Debian maintainers deliberately excluded this feature from the bullseye build
+4. **Cannot Exploit**: No code path exists to trigger the vulnerability
+
+---
+
+## **Evidence from Debian Security Tracker**
+
+Direct quote from [Debian Security Tracker](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2023-23914):
+
+> **[bullseye] - curl `<ignored>` (curl is not built with HSTS support)**
+
+This official designation confirms that:
+- The vulnerability is **ignored** for bullseye (not flagged as needing fixes)
+- The reason is explicit: **HSTS support is not built**
+- Debian security team has already determined this is not a concern for bullseye
+
+---
+
+### **Recommended: Mark as False Positive**
+- Add CVE-2023-23914 to your scanner's false positive/exception list for Debian bullseye curl
+- Document the reasoning: "HSTS functionality not compiled in Debian bullseye build"
+- Reference the official Debian Security Tracker determination
+- Monitor for any changes in future Debian bullseye curl updates that might include HSTS support
+
+---
+**References:**
+- [Debian Security Tracker - CVE-2023-23914](https://security-tracker.debian.org/tracker/CVE-2023-23914)
+- [curl CVE-2023-23914 Advisory](https://curl.se/docs/CVE-2023-23914.html)
